org.gearvrf

Enum GVRImportSettings

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<GVRImportSettings>
      • org.gearvrf.GVRImportSettings
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<GVRImportSettings>

    public enum GVRImportSettings
extends java.lang.Enum<GVRImportSettings>
    Encapsulates Assimp import settings to be passed in to GVRAssetLoader. Do not change these values since they must match values defined in Assimp's postprocess.h

    • Enum Constant Summary

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • CALCULATE_TANGENTS

        public static final GVRImportSettings CALCULATE_TANGENTS
        Tell Importer to calculate tangents in case they are not present in imported model. This is required for bump map as most models won't have tangents exported.

      • JOIN_IDENTICAL_VERTICES

        public static final GVRImportSettings JOIN_IDENTICAL_VERTICES
        Tell Importer to join vertices when possible. The least vertex elements you have present in the mesh the highest the probability vertices will be joined. This setting should always be on since it will reduce number of vertices sent to be processed by graphics pipeline.

      • TRIANGULATE

        public static final GVRImportSettings TRIANGULATE
        Tell Importer to Triangulate mesh. Triangle meshes are most suitable for rendering performance and this settings should be always on.

      • CALCULATE_NORMALS

        public static final GVRImportSettings CALCULATE_NORMALS
        Tell Importer to calculate hard normals in case they are not present in imported model.

      • CALCULATE_SMOOTH_NORMALS

        public static final GVRImportSettings CALCULATE_SMOOTH_NORMALS
        Tell Importer to calculate smooth normals in case they are not present in imported model.

      • LIMIT_BONE_WEIGHT

        public static final GVRImportSettings LIMIT_BONE_WEIGHT
        Tell Importer to limit bone weight. Default value is at most 4 bone weights. This will optimize rendering of Skinned meshes.

      • IMPROVE_VERTEX_CACHE_LOCALITY

        public static final GVRImportSettings IMPROVE_VERTEX_CACHE_LOCALITY
        Tell Importer to reorder vertex indices to improve for cache locality. This will be useful for scenes with medium to high polygon meshes.

      • SORTBY_PRIMITIVE_TYPE

        public static final GVRImportSettings SORTBY_PRIMITIVE_TYPE
        Split meshes by primitive type.

      • OPTIMIZE_MESHES

        public static final GVRImportSettings OPTIMIZE_MESHES
        Optimize meshes so number of drawcalls can be reduced. Use this with OPTIMIZE_GRAPH.

      • OPTIMIZE_GRAPH

        public static final GVRImportSettings OPTIMIZE_GRAPH
        Tries to merge together nodes that don't have bones, lights, animations and cameras. This is supposed to be used with OPTIMIZE_MESHES. Note that this might lose reference to node names.

      • START_ANIMATIONS

        public static final GVRImportSettings START_ANIMATIONS
        Causes the animations in the asset to start as soon as the asset is added to the scene.

      • FLIP_UV

        public static final GVRImportSettings FLIP_UV
        Flip UV mapping in y direction.

      • NO_LIGHTING

        public static final GVRImportSettings NO_LIGHTING
        Do not include light sources and omit vertex normals from meshes

      • NO_ANIMATION

        public static final GVRImportSettings NO_ANIMATION
        Do not include animations and omit bone weights and indices from meshes

      • NO_TEXTURING

        public static final GVRImportSettings NO_TEXTURING
        Do not include textures and omit texture coordinates from meshes

      • getAssimpImportFlags

        public static int getAssimpImportFlags(java.util.EnumSet<GVRImportSettings> settings)
        This will convert the provided enum settings to assimp bitwise format. Only flags used by Assimp are processed, others are ignored. It's highly recommended to use one of the predefined settings fuctions lie getRecommendedSettings or if you want additional settings use getRecommendedSettingsWith(EnumSet).
        Parameters:
        settings - EnumSet of all import settings desired
        Returns:
        flag in the assimp import format.

      • getRecommendedSettings

        public static java.util.EnumSet<GVRImportSettings> getRecommendedSettings()
        Return recommended settings for simple meshes. If you need bumpmapped meshes use getRecommendedBumpmapSettings()
        Returns:
        EnumSet of recommended settings.
